Privacy Policy
Effective Date: September 12, 2022
This Privacy Policy covers the Personal Information practices of any website (including,
https://youappi.com/
) that links to this Privacy Policy (severally and jointly, the “
Site
”) and is operated by YouAppi Inc. or its affiliates and subsidiaries companies (“
YouAppi
”, “
we
”, “
us
” or “
ours
”), and the advertising services (the “
Services
”) that YouAppi provides to its supply and demand partners.
In this Privacy Policy, Personal Information is any combination of information, in the possession of or likely to come into the possession of YouAppi, that can be used to identify, contact, or locate a discrete individual (“
Personal Information
”).  Personal Information includes any expression of opinion about an individual. Generally speaking, information that does not identify a discrete individual (such as aggregated statistical information) is not considered Personal Information. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully, before using the Site or the Services, so you can fully understand our practices in relation to Personal Information, before we begin processing your information.
Important note
: Nothing in this Privacy Policy is intended to limit in any way your statutory right, including your rights to a remedy or means of enforcement.
This Privacy Policy explains
:
WHAT PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND HOW WE USE IT
DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION TO OTHERS
TRANSFERS TO THIRD COUNTRIES
YOUR RIGHTS
YOUR ADVERTISEMENT OPT OUT CHOICES
HOW WE PROTECT YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
DO NOT TRACK
EXTERNAL LINKS
USE BY CHILDREN
HOW TO CONTACT US
CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY
The information gathered by YouAppi from the Site is either Personal Information voluntarily supplied by Site users or tracking information gathered as users navigate through the Site. In these instances, YouAppi is considered a data controller of this Personal Information. Please note that you are not required by law to provide us with any such Personal Information.
YouAppi is a company that provides mobile app developers with user acquisition and retargeting services to grow their businesses. In addition, when you use the Services as a demand partner or supply partner, YouAppi collects Personal Information about your end users in order to provide you with the Services. When collecting this Personal Information, YouAppi acts as a processor of this Personal Information. If you are an individual, using YouAppi's Services as a result of our relationship with YouAppi’s customer ("
Individual(s)
"), please note that the customer is the responsible party for obtaining the required consents and complying with any applicable laws or regulations.
1. WHAT PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND HOW WE USE IT.
(I) Personal Information voluntarily provided by you on the Site.
When using the Site, you can provide us with Personal Information to help us serve your needs.  The Personal Information that we collect will depend on how you use the Site. For the purposes listed below, YouAppi acts as a data controller.
a) When you submit Personal Information and/or a request via our Site
Personal Information collected and for which purposes. Legal basis
: When you request Personal Information about our Services (including, contact us form, request a demo, you must submit your full name, phone number, company details (to the extent that it contains Personal Information) and e-mail address. In addition, if you insert the reason for your communication that could contain additional Personal Information (provided voluntarily by you). The legal basis are: processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is party or in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract and our legitimate interest in answering your questions and inquires. We will use this Personal Information to:
Determine whether you are an existing client of YouAppi;
Send you the material you have requested;
Assist you in the completion of your application;
Assess your eligibility for any requested service
Responding to your inquiries about accounts and other Services; and
Making proposals for future service needs.
Also, we will send you marketing communications (in accordance with your consent)
Third parties with whom we share your Personal Information
: Wordpress, Salesforce, Hubspot, AWS and Outreach.io.
Retention period
: We will retain your Personal Information for the amount of time necessary in order to process your inquiries and respond to your requests. If we have not received a communication from you within 9 months, or you have asked to delete your Personal Information, we will delete records of your Personal Information, please note that in some circumstances we may store your Personal Data for longer periods of time.
Consequences of not providing the Personal Information
: We cannot (i) Determine whether you are an existing client of YouAppi; (ii) send you the material you have requested; (iii) assist you in the completion of your application; (iv) assess your eligibility for any requested service; (v) responding to your inquiries about accounts and other Services; (vi) making proposals for future service needs; and (vii) send you marketing communications (in accordance with your consent).
b) When you register to our Services
Personal Information collected and for which purposes. Legal basis
: Following an inquiry into receiving the Services from us and when you register to proceed with the Services, we ask you for your name, your position and the organization you work for, e-mail address, country, postcode, telephone number, billing address or payment details.
The legal basis for processing this Personal Information are: the performance of a contract with you and our legitimate interest in providing you the Services requested by you. We use this Personal Information to:
Provide and maintain the Service to you, including performing payment processing operations (through third party service providers);
Renew the Service;
Establish and maintain communications with you and other users;
Make proposals for future service and product needs;
To create users for your use of our platform/dashboard
To perform/execute the agreement
To grant you and your admin users access to the services (our platform/dashboard)
To manage your everyday business needs (e.g., administration of your users / log-in to the Services)
Third parties with whom we share your Personal Information:
AWS for cloud purposes; Hubspot and SalesForce for CRM purposes.
Retention period
: To the extent that you are using the Services, we will store your Personal Information for the period in which you have an account with us to provide you with the Services. After you close your account, we will retain your Personal Information only to the extent required or allowed by applicable law.
Consequences of not providing the Personal Information
: We cannot (i) provide and maintain the Service to you; (ii) renew the Services; (iii) establish and maintain communications with you and other users; (iv) make proposals for future service and product needs; and/or (v) allow our affiliated companies to notify you of certain products or Services they offer.
c) When you are a candidate and you submit your CV
Personal Information collected and for which purposes. Legal basis
: Full name, email address, phone number, resume/CV, LinkedIn profile and any other information that you decide to provide/supply us. The legal basis for processing this Personal Information are: Performance of a contract to which the data subject is party or in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract. Legitimate interest (e.g. to assess a candidate). We use this Personal Information to
:
Process your job application, and
Assess the candidate.
Note
: For the avoidance of doubt, this use case shall apply to the CVs submitted by the Website or by any other methods (e.g., HR and recruitment agencies).
Third parties with whom we share your Personal Information:
LinkedIn and Fresh Team.
Retention period:
Your Personal Information will be stored until we delete the record and we proactively delete it or you send a valid deletion request please note that in some circumstances we may store your Personal Information for longer periods of time, for example (i) where we are required to do so in accordance with legal, regulatory, tax or accounting requirements, or (ii) for us to have an accurate record of your dealings with us in the event of any complaints or challenges, or (iii) if we reasonably believe there is a prospect of litigation relating to your Personal Information or dealings.
Consequences of not providing the Personal Information
: We cannot (i) process your job application and (ii) assess you as a candidate.
(II) Tracking Information when users navigate the Site.
As you navigate this Site, we also use commonly-used information-gathering tools, such as cookies and web beacons to operate the Site and provide you with certain features and functionalities. These tools collect standard information from your web browser (such as browser type and browser language), your Internet Protocol (“IP”) address and the actions you take on the Site (such as the web pages viewed and the links clicked). The legal basis for processing this information is for the performance of a contract with you and our legitimate interest in being able to provide and improve the functionalities of the Site offered to you. If you are located in the European Union, we also rely on your consent to use cookies. Like many companies, we uses cookies on the Site. Cookies are pieces of information shared between your web browser and the Site.  Cookies enable us to offer a faster and easier user experience. For more information about the cookies that we use, please visit our cookie notice
https://youappi.com/cookie-policy/
Google Analytics
. The Website uses a tool called “Google Analytics” to collect information about use of the Website. Google Analytics collects information such as how often users visit this Website, what pages they visit when they do so, and what other websites they used prior to coming to this Website. We use the information we get from Google Analytics to maintain and improve the Website and our products. We do not combine the information collected through the use of Google Analytics with Personal Information we collect. Google’s ability to use and share information collected by Google Analytics about your visits to this Website is restricted by the Google Analytics Terms of Service, available at
https://marketingplatform.google.com/about/analytics/terms/us/
, and the Google Privacy Policy, available at
http://www.google.com/policies/privacy/
. You may learn more about how Google collects and processes data specifically in connection with Google Analytics at
http://www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/
. You may prevent your data from being used by Google Analytics by downloading and installing the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on, available at
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/
.
(III) Personal Information when our customer make use of the Services.
a) When we provide our services to our customers.
Personal Information collected and for which purposes
: When you make use of the Services as a demand partner or supply partner, YouAppi collects Personal Information about your end users in order to provide you with the Services. YouAppi collects or receives information about the end user’s device and the ads it view or click. The Services are designed to avoid collecting information that identifies you personally, such as your name, address, or email address, but the information we collect may enable us to recognize your device over time. YouAppi’s Services collects (depending on the case) the following categories of end user Personal Information:
Mobile Advertising ID for Services performed via a mobile device; and
IP address. We also collect other non-Personal Information in providing the Services including:
Device make, model and operating system;
Device properties related to screen size & orientation, audio volume and battery;
Carrier;
Operating system;
Name and properties of mobile application through which a consumer interacts with the Services;
Country, time zone and locale settings (country and preferred language);
Network connection type and speed;
Activity of a user on an application following installation; and
Internet browser user-agent used to access the Services.
Services to Supply Partners
: YouAppi uses these Personal Information to find and serve the optimal advertisement for the end user of your mobile website or application (the “
Property
”). In addition, YouAppi passes these Personal Information on to the Advertiser’s tracking vendor for tracking purposes so that an install event can be detected (which then triggers a payment to you, i.e., the Supply Partner). Please note that YouAppi only collects Personal Information from the Property to the extent that you, our customer, have instructed  YouAppi (in accordance with the permissions you have activated inside the Property) to collect, use and share the Personal Information with advertisers, demand partners and other relevant third parties, in order to provide the Services and.
Services to Demand Partners
: YouAppi uses these Personal Information to facilitate and optimize campaigns for advertisers across its network. It only uses the Personal Information provided by a demand partner to optimize campaigns for this demand partner – YouAppi does not cross-use Personal Information received from one advertiser to optimize the campaigns of another advertiser. YouAppi will receive Personal Information from your tracking vendor on whether an event which triggers payment to YouAppi or measures quality of the installs provided by YouAppi has occurred on a Property. This is so we can serve your advertisement on the Properties of our supply partners and pay them for certain events agreed between us (e.g., installs, certain interactions on a Property etc). YouAppi shares the Personal Information with advertisers, measurement/attribution partners, and with our technical infrastructure vendor (AWS), for the purpose of providing our Services.
Additional processing activities
: We also use these Personal Information to detect and prevent fraudulent actions of end users. For example, we will detect multiple requests from a certain piece of information (e.g., IP address) that could not reasonably be performed by a human being in such time or volume.
Third parties with whom we share your Personal Information
: (i) With advertisers and demand partners (including advertisers, and measurement/attribution partners) for the purposes of providing our Services; (ii) aggregated and non-Personal Information: We share aggregate or non-personally identifiable information about the use of our Services with the relevant customer. For example, we provide advertisers reports showing how many users viewed or clicked on their ads. We also provide publishers reports about the types of ads served to their mobile apps; and (iv) with our vendors and service providers to provide the Services, such as providing technical infrastructure services.
Retention period
: We will retain the Personal Information described above for the life of an active campaign and for six (6) months thereafter, or until you (our customer) instruct us otherwise to delete such Personal Information, noting that we will continue to retain your Personal Information for longer periods only to the extent required or allowed by applicable law or auditing requirements.
The iOS mobile devices may provide an 'App Tracking Transparency' setting. On Android devices, your settings may allow you to 'Opt out of Interest-Based Ads.' When you, as an Individual, have opted out using this setting on a device, YouAppi will not use in-app information collected from that device to infer your interests or serve ads to that device that are targeted based on your inferred interests.
Note
: For the avoidance of doubt, we will process the Personal Data stated in this use case on behalf of our customers when providing the services to them. If you have any questions regarding this processing, please note that the Customer is the responsible party for obtaining the required consents and complying with any applicable laws or regulations. Therefore, you should closely review the privacy policies of the applications and websites that you make use in order to learn about the privacy practices of our Customers.
(IV) When we use the Personal Information of our customers (e.g. contact details)
Personal Information collected and for which purposes. Legal basis
: When our customer supply us with information containing third-party Personal Information (names, addresses, or other Personal Information relating to living individuals) excluding Personal Information of end users provided in connection with your use of the Services, we will hold and use such Personal Information to perform Services and communicate with you (our customer) on the understanding that the individuals to whom the Personal Information relates have been informed of the reason for which you shared such Personal Information with us.
Third parties with whom we share your Personal Information:
Amazon Web Services, Google, Salesforce, Hubspot.
Retention period
: We will retain the Personal Information described above for the period in which we have an active business relationship with you or until you ask us to delete such data, note that we may receive consent directly from the data subject of such Personal Information, in which case the retention period and use shall be governed by our relationship with such data subject.
Consequences of not providing the Personal Information
: We cannot provide you with the services and to send you service-related communications.
(v) When you attend a marketing event and/or we exchange business cards and you provide us with your Personal Information
Personal Information collected and for which purposes. Legal basis
: First name, last name, email address, company name, contact information, and any other data you decide to supply. The legal basis for processing this Personal Information are: depending on the context consent and/or legitimate interest (e.g. to send you B2B communications). We use this Personal Information to:
Establish a business connection;
Allow you to participate in webinar and other events that we organize (including, to send you event-related communications); and
Send you marketing communications
